info.senderName: NWS Duluth (Northeast Minnesota and Northern Wisconsin)
info.headline: Lakeshore Flood Watch issued October 12 at 4:13PM CDT until October 14 at 4:00AM CDT by NWS Duluth
info.description: ...LAKESHORE FLOOD WATCH REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM FRIDAY MORNING THROUGH LATE FRIDAY NIGHT... * WHAT...Lakeshore flooding possible. * WHERE...Canal Park to Bayfront Festival Park and areas in between within the city of Duluth. * WHEN...From Friday morning through late Friday night. * IMPACTS...Large waves of 10 to 15 feet and water levels around 603 ft at the Duluth water level station and prolonged gale force wind gusts out of the northeast will result in piling up of water in the Twin Ports area which may result in coastal flooding. Portions of Canal Park, Harbor Drive behind the DECC and Helberg Drive may become flooded.
info.instruction: Do not drive around barricades or through water of unknown depth. Take the necessary actions to protect flood-prone property.
